License: MIT

Comment:
 This convenience package statically links its Rust dependencies (the binary
 is built with cargo). Their licenses, choosing MIT where a crate is dual
 MIT/Apache-2.0, reduce to: MIT and BSD-3-Clause (subtle) and Unicode-3.0
 (unicode-ident). An official Debian package would instead use dh-cargo /
 debcargo with each crate packaged separately (no bundling).

